  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships postinstall beacon scripts that exfiltrate host data",
  "details": "Package declares a postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") that executes on every install. The tarball additionally ships beacon34.js and beacon_linux.js, both of which combine require('child_process') + require('http')/require('https') with reads of process.env, process.platform, os.hostname(), and os.platform(), and issue HTTP GET/POST requests (e.g., http.get(...) at beacon_linux.js:94/144 and http.request(...) at line 282). The naming, structure, and behavior of these files are consistent with host-information beacons that send installer environment variables, hostname, and platform identifiers to a remote endpoint at install time. There is no legitimate functionality declared for the package that would justify auto-executing system-info collectors on install.",
